# UI Standards

## Theme

- Background: near-black `#0a0a0a` / `bg-[#0a0a0a]`
- Accent: amber/gold — `amber-500` / `#f59e0b` (one accent; no new brand colors)
- Text: white headings, `text-gray-400` secondary
- Brand name in UI: **Podium AI**

## Layout

- **Public:** landing (`components/landing/**`) — full-width marketing sections
- **Auth:** `components/auth/**` inside `AuthShell` — login / signup / Google OAuth
- **App:** `app/(protected)/**` with `components/dashboard/sidebar.tsx` + `top-bar.tsx` on dashboard; feature pages own their main content
- Mobile-first: stack below `768px` (`md:` breakpoints)

## Component Rules

- Functional components only
- Tailwind utilities only; no inline `style=`
- `lucide-react` for icons
- `@elevenlabs/react` only in `components/voice-coach/**` (ConvAI session UI)
- No new UI libraries (shadcn, MUI, etc.) without agreement

## States

Every interactive flow should cover:

| State | Behaviour |
|-------|-----------|
| idle | Default, awaiting action |
| loading | Spinner/skeleton; disable inputs |
| ready | Data loaded; user can proceed |
| active | Recording, TTS playing, or live voice session |

Use `transition` / `duration-*` between states.

## Errors & API calls from the client

- Show errors in the UI (`AuthAlert`, inline messages) — not `alert()` or console-only
- `fetch('/api/…')` then `parseApiJson(res)`; handle `error`, `warning`, and domain codes (e.g. `unclear_audio`)
- Loading indicators for every async step (analyze, speak, signed-url, end-session)

## Feature-specific UI

- **Speech eval:** `app/(protected)/speech-eval/components/` — `TopicSetup`, `Recorder`, `FeedbackCards`; voice picks from `lib/speech-eval.ts`
- **Voice coach:** `components/voice-coach/` — mode selection, session, end-session flow
- **Dashboard:** `components/dashboard/` — stats, practice cards, action points panel

Match existing patterns in `components/` — do not redesign unless asked.
